0.5     FIVE YEAR ACCIDENT HISTORY    


The GE Quartz Plant has an outstanding record of accident prevention that demonstrates its commitment to public and worker safety.  Even minor incidents are investigated to identify root cause and corrective or preventative actions.

The RMP requires that all incidents involving regulated chemicals that resulted in any off-site impact or significant on-site impacts be reported in this document.  GE Quartz has had no releases of HF acid at the Quartz Plant within this 5-year history that resulted in any on-site or off-site impacts as defined by EPA.


0.6     PARTICIPATION IN EMERGENCY RESPONSE

The GE Quartz Plant is included in the community response plan of the Local Emergency Planning Commission (LEPC).  Plant staff are trained as first responders to a spill and the Plant has agreements with spill contractors for emergency response assistance.


